questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application's service method is silently failing to commit database transactions. The method is annotated with `@Transactional`, but data is not persisting to the database. The code is written as follows:

java
@Service
public class UserService {
    @Autowired
    private UserRepository userRepository;

    @Transactional
    public CompletableFuture<User> createUser(String name) {
        return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> {
            User user = new User(name);
            return userRepository.save(user); 
        });
    }
}
